Paper Title: Effects of Safety State Augmentation on Safe Exploration

Paper Abstract: 

Paper Section Text:
Environments: We use the safe pendulum environment defined in [ref]16, and we also use the custom-made safety gym environment with deterministic constraints, which we call static point goal 1. In this environment with 464646 states and 222 actions, a large hazard circle is placed before the goal and forces the agent to go around it to reach the goal similarly to our cartoon in Figure 1. We provide additional details in
Figure 2 and
Appendix. The rest of our tests are performed on the safety gym benchmarks [ref]37. Code base: Our code is based on two repositories: safety starter agents [ref]37, and PID Lagrangian . The code for PI Simmer and Q Simmer is available at https://github.com/huawei-noah/HEBO/tree/master/SIMMER. We use default parameters for both code bases unless stated otherwise. Computational resources: We performed all computations on a PC equipped with 512GB of RAM, two Intel Xeon E5 CPUs, and four 16GB NVIDIA Tesla V100 GPUs. Baselines (∙∙\bullet) and our algorithms (■■\blacksquare):
  ∙∙\bullet CPO, Lagrangian PPO (L-PPO), and TRPO (L-TRPO); Standard baselines from [ref]37;
  ∙∙\bullet PID-Lagrangian. An algorithm stabilizing L-PPO learning ;
  ∙∙\bullet LAMBDA. A model-based method showing great performance on Safety Gym ;
  ∙∙\bullet PO-PPO PPO-based algorithm with probability one constraints from ; 
  ■■\blacksquare PI-Simmer  - Scheduling safety budget using PI controller for PO-PPO;
  ■■\blacksquare Q-Simmer - Scheduling safety budget using Q learning for PO-PPO; 
  ■■\blacksquare L-PPO (PID-L) w SA  - L-PPO (PID-L) solving Problem 2 with safety state augmentation;
  ■■\blacksquare Simmer L-PPO (PID-L) - L-PPO (PID-L) w SA and safety budget scheduling.

